<subSubSection id="AEC4F09E990CFFABFD15FA8BF10EC29F" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="238" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E661A315990CFFAAFD15FA8BF077C1BE" blockId="2.[675,1211,1388,1700]" box="[677,777,1388,1415]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E661A315990CFFAAFD15FA6BF0E6C29F" blockId="2.[675,1211,1388,1700]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<taxonomicName id="21DED896990CFFAAFD15FA6BF001C19D" box="[677,895,1420,1446]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Rhipsalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="D4AA7F07990CFFAAFD15FA6BF001C19D" box="[677,895,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Rhipsalis triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was documented for the first time in its natural habitat in 1996, during an expedition to Pedra Branca Massif, in southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="9EC9E385990CFFAAFBC5FA2CF7C8C1DD" box="[1141,1206,1483,1510]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Searches for the species were intensified over the following years in the region, and this has resulted in new collections in the neighbouring area of the Prainha Municipal Natural Park and Pedra Branca State Park, both located on the 
<collectingRegion id="241A6DF7990CFFAAFC59F98EF7C6C2BF" box="[1001,1208,1641,1668]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Rio de Janeiro State</collectingRegion>
coast in 
<collectingCountry id="9EC9E385990CFFAAFD4CF96EF044C29F" box="[764,826,1673,1700]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="7EE5BF90990CFFAAFCF9F96EF0F4C29F" box="[841,906,1673,1700]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[677,688,1055,1072]" captionTargetBox="[677,1209,215,1013]" captionTargetId="figure-496@2.[676,1209,214,1013]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 2.– Rhipsalis triangularis Werderm.in its natural habitat (Pedra Branca Massif, Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4601424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4601424/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="B2A1F39D990DFFABFF31FC5EF107C7F1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4601426" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4601426" box="[129,633,953,970]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4601426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" startId="3.[129,140,953,970]" targetBox="[113,646,215,920]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="E661A315990DFFABFF31FC5EF107C7F1" blockId="3.[129,633,953,970]" box="[129,633,953,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
FIG. 3. – Flowers and buds of 
<taxonomicName id="21DED896990DFFABFEC7FC5EF107C7F1" authority="Werderm." box="[375,633,953,970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Rhipsalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="D4AA7F07990DFFABFEC7FC5EF15CC7F1" box="[375,546,953,970]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">Rhipsalis triangularis</emphasis>
Werderm.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E661A315990DFFABFF38FC17F233C0B1" blockId="3.[111,649,1008,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
These recent discoveries allowed 
<bibRefCitation id="824FDEE4990DFFABFE6DFC17F27DC010" author="CALVENTE A. M. &amp; ANDREATA R. H. P." pageId="3" pageNumber="238" pagination="529 - 548" refId="ref1335" refString="CALVENTE A. M. &amp; ANDREATA R. H. P. 2007. - The Cactaceae of the Natural Municipal Park of Prainha, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil: taxonomy and conservation. Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 1: 529 - 548." type="journal article" year="2007">Calvente &amp; Andreata (2007)</bibRefCitation>
to describe the 
<taxonomicName id="21DED896990DFFABFE00FBE8F1F8C012" box="[432,646,1039,1065]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Rhipsalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="D4AA7F07990DFFABFE00FBE8F1F8C012" box="[432,646,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">Rhipsalis triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphology and natural habitat in detail, but these authors did not address the question of formal typification of the name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E661A315990DFFABFF38FB69F292C1FD" blockId="3.[111,649,1008,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
<taxonomicName id="21DED896990DFFABFF38FB69F225C093" box="[136,347,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Rhipsalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="D4AA7F07990DFFABFF38FB69F225C093" box="[136,347,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">Rhipsalis triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a heliophyte species which forms dense islands of vegetation on the rocky outcrops (
<figureCitation id="7EE5BF90990DFFABFFC6FB29F3CCC0D2" box="[118,178,1230,1257]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[677,688,1055,1072]" captionTargetBox="[677,1209,215,1013]" captionTargetId="figure-496@2.[676,1209,214,1013]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 2.– Rhipsalis triangularis Werderm.in its natural habitat (Pedra Branca Massif, Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4601424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4601424/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) or appears rarely as epiphytes on sunlit open canopy trees. Th is species probably reproduces also vegetatively and the basal stem segments sometimes have the margins lacerated (
<bibRefCitation id="824FDEE4990DFFABFE2DFACAF3D0C15C" author="CALVENTE A. M. &amp; ANDREATA R. H. P." pageId="3" pageNumber="238" pagination="529 - 548" refId="ref1335" refString="CALVENTE A. M. &amp; ANDREATA R. H. P. 2007. - The Cactaceae of the Natural Municipal Park of Prainha, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil: taxonomy and conservation. Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 1: 529 - 548." type="journal article" year="2007">Calvente &amp; Andreata 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The flowers are white, abundant and visited by many different species of bees (
<figureCitation id="7EE5BF90990DFFABFE73FA8BF281C1BC" box="[451,511,1388,1415]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[129,140,953,970]" captionTargetBox="[113,646,215,920]" captionTargetId="figure-588@3.[113,646,215,920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 3. – Flowers and buds of Rhipsalis triangularis Werderm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4601426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4601426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The flowers and fruits are synchronic and collected along April, May, June, October and November.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E661A315990DFFABFF38FA2CF10EC29F" blockId="3.[111,649,1008,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
According to the 
<bibRefCitation id="824FDEE4990DFFABFE8DFA2CF2ACC1DD" author="IUCN" box="[317,466,1483,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" refId="ref1703" refString="IUCN 2001. - IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland, Switzerland, Cambridge, UK, ii + 30 p." type="book" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, 
<taxonomicName id="21DED896990DFFABFD9DFA2CF398C23E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Rhipsalis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="D4AA7F07990DFFABFD9DFA2CF398C23E" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">Rhipsalis triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is categorized as critically endangered – CR (B2b), with a known occupation area of less than 
<quantity id="21260EF0990DFFABFF18F9CDF391C27E" box="[168,239,1578,1605]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
². Th is species is also listed in the CITES checklist (
<bibRefCitation id="824FDEE4990DFFABFF65F9ADF233C25E" author="HUNT D." box="[213,333,1610,1637]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" refId="ref1613" refString="HUNT D. 1992. - CITES Cactaceae Checklist. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, 190 p." type="book" year="1992">Hunt 1992</bibRefCitation>
), although it is not included in the recent offi cial lists of Brazilian species threatened with extinction (i.e. 
<bibRefCitation id="824FDEE4990DFFABFEF5F96EF2BCC29F" author="COSTA L. H. P." box="[325,450,1673,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" refId="ref1523" refString="COSTA L. H. P. 2000. - Cactaceae, in Di Maio F. R. &amp; Silva M. B. R. (eds), Especies ameacadas de extincao no municipio do Rio de Janeiro: Flora e Fauna. Secretaria Municipal do Meio Ambiente, Rio de Janeiro: 22." type="book" year="2000">Costa 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="824FDEE4990DFFABFE7DF96EF11AC29F" author="IBAMA" box="[461,612,1673,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" refId="ref1670" refString="IBAMA. 2008. - Instrucao normativa nº 6 / 2008. (http: // www. ibama. gov. br / sisbio, last accessed 28 July 2009)." type="url" year="2008">IBAMA 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
